analysis: The documents primarily concern land management and resource allocation in Alaska, with a focus on transferring, withdrawing, reserving, and modifying land use for various governmental purposes including military, naval, agricultural, forestry, and townsite development. Many documents involve specific geographical coordinates and legal descriptions of land parcels. A recurring theme is the modification or revocation of previous executive orders related to land use.
title: Alaskan Land Reallocations and Reservations
